64.6	True_Grit_(novel)	True Grit (novel)	True Grit is a 1968 novel by Charles Portis that was first published as a 1968 serial in The Saturday Evening Post. The novel is told from the perspective of a woman named Mattie Ross who recounts the time when she was 14 years old and sought retribution for the murder of her father by a scoundrel named Tom Chaney. It is considered by many critics to be "one of the great American novels".	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/2/2b/True_Grit.jpg/220px-True_Grit.jpg
